items.description: The SSD-120-30N altitude digitizer is designed to be mounted within a pressurized or non-pressurized, but temperature controlled area within aircraft operating up to 42,000 feet MSL. Usually remotely located, the digitizer is fully automatic in operation. The parallel ICAO altitude data output is controlled by the transponder.

items.itemId: menu2-cat2-1-antenna-erosion-masks-450- Research -586 Boeing BBJ SATCOM Base Fairing Erosion Film--586
items.name: Research -586 Boeing BBJ SATCOM Base Fairing Erosion Film
items.description: M Research -586 EMS SATCOM Antenna Base Fairing Film ill fit the following aircraft: oeing BBJ.  Research Films are made from a clear, self-adhesive Polyurethane that is .012 of an inch thick. The Polyurethane is not affected by UV light, meaning it will never yellow and it will not change the cosmetic appearance of your aircraft. The Film is easy to install by peeling off the backing and wetting the material with a solution of distilled water, alcohol and dish washing liquid, and you can fly within an hour of installation. An 11 page instruction booklet comes with each Film giving detailed installation instructions. Shelf life is 5+ years.

items.itemId: menu2-cat3-1-antennas-242-Cobham Comant CI-105-16 DME / Transponder Antenna-CI105-16
items.name: Cobham Comant CI-105-16 DME / Transponder Antenna
items.description: Broadband and rugged antenna designed for DME or transponder use. The CI 105-16 was designed specifically for the Honeywell Bendix-King™ KA60. This unit offers the extended length, two stud mounting found on the KA60. Tested to the tougher DO-160D environmental requirements, this antenna offers the best in ruggedness and performance.

items.itemId: menu2-cat4-1-aviation-elt-2444-ACR Artex™ 8207 Model ELT 1000 406 MHz Emergency Locator Transmitter - Rod Antenna & ACE Switch-8207
items.name: ACR Artex™ 8207 Model ELT 1000 406 MHz Emergency Locator Transmitter - Rod Antenna & ACE Switch
items.description: Artex's ELT 1000 is an excellent, cost-efficient option for upgrading standard 121.5 MHz transmitters, which are longer monitored by the Cospas-Sarsat System. The ELT 1000 is a single-output ELT that transmits on both 406 MHz and 121.5 MHz using the same RF output and one coax cable. The 406 signal alone produces an accurate position within 1.86 miles and when paired with the aircraft's navigation system via the built-in GPS interface, the ELT's accuracy is further improved to about 110 yards. The GPS interface does not require aircraft power to operate and the remote switch only requires two wires, which reduces installation costs and labor.
